MatchedRegions.transcript: Lastly, we examine the discrimination power of different concepts.
We found that the same concept usually pushes the classification of different samples towards the same category.

MatchedRegion.Text: For each concept S, if the concept is saliently activated on a set of samples, then interaction effects I (S) of the same concept are supposed to push the classification of these samples towards the same category in most cases.
The average discrimination power B of concepts was usually higher than 0.8, which verified the discrimination power of extracted concepts.
